text: Sok Chanraksmey (, born 10 January 1992) is a former Cambodian footballer who last played for Asia Euro United in the Cambodian League. ==International career== He made his senior international debut on 24 March 2013 in a 2014 AFC Challenge Cup qualification match against Philippines. He scored his first international goal in a friendly match against Malaysia. He scored all three goals for his country in 2014 AFF Suzuki Cup qualification match against Timor-Leste which his country came behind to win that match 3-2. ==International goals== {| class="wikitable" style="font-size:90%" ! # !!
